20:21.512 --> 20:23.680
Where's my mom?!

20:23.681 --> 20:25.140
Did I pass chem?

20:25.141 --> 20:27.392
Anyway... hi.

20:27.393 --> 20:30.129
What did you wanna tell me earlier?

20:31.021 --> 20:32.313
Nothing.

20:32.314 --> 20:34.886
Are you okay, you seem
a little off your game.

20:35.359 --> 20:37.193
I... I think I'm a little sick.

20:37.194 --> 20:38.987
You know, I think I
might have a stomach ache.

20:38.988 --> 20:40.113
Yeah, I feel ya.

20:40.114 --> 20:41.322
I don't think I cooked those beetles

20:41.323 --> 20:43.366
all the way through last night.

20:43.367 --> 20:45.702
- Good luck out there.
- What do I do with this?!

20:45.703 --> 20:46.995
God!

20:46.996 --> 20:49.080
Waste of a pointy stick if you ask me.

20:50.249 --> 20:51.708
Have a good day, honey.

20:51.709 --> 20:53.182
Smooches?

20:53.878 --> 20:55.420
Looks like

20:55.421 --> 20:57.019
we're in for some weather.

20:58.112 --> 21:00.383
See you at home, I love you!

21:14.191 --> 21:15.565
My God.

21:15.566 --> 21:17.984
My God, wake up, my God.

21:17.985 --> 21:19.652
What do I know about babies?

21:19.653 --> 21:20.737
I don't know anything about babies.

21:20.738 --> 21:21.988
You're not my baby.

21:21.989 --> 21:23.406
You're not!

21:28.078 --> 21:29.204
You're my baby.

21:31.207 --> 21:33.041
What is happening?

21:33.042 --> 21:35.084
What is happening, what is happening?

21:36.378 --> 21:38.588
Dad, I need Dad, I need Dad.

21:43.370 --> 21:45.428
My God.

21:46.597 --> 21:47.847
Dad?

21:51.212 --> 21:52.910
_

22:15.125 --> 22:16.918
You've got this, Val.

22:16.919 --> 22:19.126
You're a bad-ass bitch.

22:19.732 --> 22:21.464
I need you right now.

22:23.634 --> 22:25.051
Keep it together.

22:27.555 --> 22:29.063
Sheriff?

22:30.349 --> 22:32.100
Sheriff, let's go!

22:34.824 --> 22:38.744
Tick-tock, we're late for latrine duty.

22:39.400 --> 22:41.526
Latrine duty?

22:41.527 --> 22:44.571
As in... scrubbing toilets.

22:44.596 --> 22:48.123
Hey, if you can call 'em that.

22:48.148 --> 22:49.784
But I'm... the sheriff?

22:49.785 --> 22:50.994
I'm the sheriff.

22:50.995 --> 22:54.122
Yeah, and sanitation commissioner

22:54.123 --> 22:56.666
and a scavenger and a mom.

22:56.667 --> 22:58.793
Hey, you got a lot going on,

22:58.794 --> 23:01.549
so shake a leg.

23:02.423 --> 23:05.925
Or do I have to toss you
out into the wasteland?

23:15.686 --> 23:17.854
- I'm gonna go get ready.
- All right, Sheriff.

23:17.855 --> 23:19.230
Come on, let's go.

23:19.231 --> 23:21.524
- Couple minutes.
- All right.

23:56.894 --> 23:58.686
Bye.

24:11.575 --> 24:13.451
Sheriff!

24:13.452 --> 24:14.610
Open up!

24:52.074 --> 24:54.117
How was your day, Mom?

24:54.118 --> 24:55.493
Fine.

24:55.494 --> 24:56.953
It was fine.

24:56.954 --> 24:59.488
Look, Mommy, I made this for you.

25:01.125 --> 25:02.416
Great.

25:03.002 --> 25:04.769
At least it's not a dog turd.

25:09.508 --> 25:12.343
Hey, Mom, did you know
the green thing in plants

25:12.344 --> 25:13.803
is this stuff called chlorophyll?

25:13.804 --> 25:16.848
Yup, I sure did... look,
Mommy's really tired

25:16.849 --> 25:18.307
and she needs to get some sleep

25:18.308 --> 25:20.785
before her 5-hour guard duty,

25:20.810 --> 25:24.480
so if you two could just...
pipe down, it'd be...

25:31.155 --> 25:33.948
Guess what, kids, it's...

25:33.949 --> 25:36.075
- Game night!
- Game night!

25:36.076 --> 25:37.577
Play Field of Fire with us!

25:37.578 --> 25:40.329
No, you leave Mommy
alone, she needs a nap.

25:40.330 --> 25:42.165
She'll play with you
next month, okay, buddy?

25:42.166 --> 25:43.583
Next month?

25:45.502 --> 25:48.504
I, could play one round.

25:48.505 --> 25:50.048
I mean, for them.

25:50.049 --> 25:51.591
"For them," right.

25:51.592 --> 25:52.717
Be sure to grab some sleep

25:52.718 --> 25:55.178
before you gotta go on guard duty, okay?

25:55.179 --> 25:56.554
Yup, yup.

25:56.555 --> 25:57.805
I'm off to the bug roast.

25:57.806 --> 25:59.348
- Have fun!
- Okay.

25:59.349 --> 26:00.683
Bye, kids.

26:12.321 --> 26:14.322
Go, Speedrun, go!

26:14.323 --> 26:16.332
Go, Speedrun, go!

26:17.326 --> 26:18.868
Not bad for an old lady?

26:18.869 --> 26:20.870
That was awesome, how are you so good?

26:20.871 --> 26:23.498
Mommy, can you teach me
how to play like that?

26:23.499 --> 26:25.166
Hell yes I can.

26:25.167 --> 26:26.834
Come here, take a seat.

26:26.835 --> 26:28.308
Sit here.

26:29.963 --> 26:33.049
Okay, first we gotta learn the basics.

26:35.886 --> 26:38.346
Okay, that's it, th... that's it.

26:38.347 --> 26:40.264
- You got it, you got it.
- Okay, you got it, you got it.

26:40.265 --> 26:42.016
Wait-wait-wait, reload, reload, reload.

26:42.017 --> 26:44.519
- Come on, reload, yes!
- Val!

26:44.520 --> 26:45.561
Val?

26:47.231 --> 26:49.065
- Thank God.
- Shit!

26:49.066 --> 26:50.650
Okay, kids, I gotta go, all right,

26:50.651 --> 26:51.901
but keep practicing.

26:51.902 --> 26:53.189
Okay.

26:53.214 --> 26:54.987
Hey, hey.

26:54.988 --> 26:56.948
Where have you been?

26:56.949 --> 26:58.324
I've been looking all over for you.

26:58.325 --> 27:00.756
- What's wrong?
- Come on.

27:00.781 --> 27:02.245
It's Dan.

27:02.246 --> 27:05.289
He was pounding on the gate
and a Death Lizard came.

27:05.290 --> 27:07.481
And you weren't there to let him in.

27:15.425 --> 27:17.343
How could you?!

27:20.639 --> 27:23.099
It was game night.

27:30.774 --> 27:32.842
No, Val, wait.

27:33.235 --> 27:35.486
You still need to finish your shift.

28:05.017 --> 28:06.268
Hi.

28:07.394 --> 28:08.699
Hi.

28:10.314 --> 28:13.066
Come to bed, hon, you
got work in the morning.

28:15.444 --> 28:18.142
I can't do this, Evan.

28:20.235 --> 28:23.826
We toil and suffer all day

28:23.827 --> 28:26.996
and if we take an extra
second for ourselves,

28:26.997 --> 28:31.334
a damn minute for a moment of peace,

28:31.335 --> 28:33.711
someone else might die?

28:33.712 --> 28:37.171
I mean... what the hell is the point?

28:38.842 --> 28:40.378
Why even bother?

28:47.893 --> 28:49.393
Val.

28:49.394 --> 28:51.801
For 12 years,

28:51.826 --> 28:54.190
you have been an amazing wife,

28:54.191 --> 28:56.751
you're an incredible mother.

28:57.402 --> 29:01.197
You are the most
fearless and thoughtful,

29:01.198 --> 29:03.449
responsible person I know.

29:05.118 --> 29:06.535
No I'm not.

29:08.455 --> 29:09.956
Yeah.

29:13.882 --> 29:15.419
Hey.

29:18.757 --> 29:22.468
One mistake doesn't change all that.

29:24.012 --> 29:26.347
Look, I could give you a speech
about why we do what we do

29:26.348 --> 29:28.599
and why we work so hard but...

29:28.600 --> 29:29.892
it'd just be words right now.

29:29.893 --> 29:32.706
You have to figure
that out for yourself.

29:32.731 --> 29:34.563
And I know that you will.

29:39.277 --> 29:41.112
I love you.

29:50.330 --> 29:51.789
Come to bed.

29:52.791 --> 29:54.396
I'll be right there.

30:37.419 --> 30:38.670
Babe?

30:42.799 --> 30:44.110
Honey?

30:51.600 --> 30:53.225
"Dear Evan..."

30:53.226 --> 30:56.187
"By the time you read
this, I'll be gone."

30:56.188 --> 30:59.099
"It pains me to leave
you and the kids, but..."

30:59.124 --> 31:01.192
"I've been living a lie."

31:02.593 --> 31:05.328
"I'm not the woman you married anymore."

31:05.864 --> 31:08.199
"I'm a 'Pulser."

31:08.200 --> 31:12.120
"You remember that FPS tournament
where I beat Roy Torvald?"

31:12.621 --> 31:15.039
"That was last Tuesday."

31:15.040 --> 31:17.166
"I thought I could hide."

31:17.167 --> 31:19.251
"I thought I could hack it."

31:19.252 --> 31:21.796
"But after last night, it's clear to me"

31:21.797 --> 31:25.007
"why you send us 'Pulsers
to the wastes to die."

31:26.843 --> 31:28.844
"There's just no place
in civilized society"

31:28.845 --> 31:32.577
"for a teenage kid trapped
in a grown-up's body,"

31:32.602 --> 31:34.850
"so I'm leaving."

31:34.851 --> 31:38.058
"Maybe I'll find another
bottle of Impulse out there."

31:38.083 --> 31:40.022
"But whatever I find,"

31:40.023 --> 31:44.424
"whatever this crazy, mixed-up
world has in store for me,"

31:44.528 --> 31:46.113
"I want you to know that I always..."

31:47.364 --> 31:49.611
Jesus Christ, Val.

32:03.380 --> 32:05.464
It's hot.

32:06.925 --> 32:08.551
So hot.

32:08.552 --> 32:10.261
What was I thinking?

32:17.060 --> 32:18.310
No way.

32:50.010 --> 32:51.470
Hey!

32:52.929 --> 32:54.630
Speedrun?

32:54.931 --> 32:56.223
Kojima?

32:56.224 --> 32:58.434
You look rough.

32:58.435 --> 33:01.641
You look... exactly the same.

33:02.606 --> 33:03.939
What the hell did you do?

33:03.940 --> 33:06.984
Well, solar panels
keep this place going.

33:06.985 --> 33:10.781
As for me, let's just
say I have my ways.

33:11.281 --> 33:13.751
So what brings you back
to my neck of the woods?

33:14.784 --> 33:18.954
I... got kicked out of my suburb.

33:18.955 --> 33:20.548
Well, that sucks.

33:21.708 --> 33:23.375
Wait a minute...

33:23.376 --> 33:25.170
did you just snap back?

33:26.796 --> 33:28.131
Last week.

33:29.466 --> 33:31.050
Damn, girl, how much did you do?

33:31.051 --> 33:32.903
You think this is funny?

33:33.220 --> 33:36.056
Your drink ruined my life!

33:38.266 --> 33:40.142
Yeah, we kinda ruined a lot of lives.

33:40.143 --> 33:42.144
- Yeah.
- I know.

33:42.145 --> 33:44.888
Um, I'll tell ya what, though.

33:45.398 --> 33:47.233
I get a lot of 'Pulsers in here, okay?

33:47.234 --> 33:49.109
Some of them are old clients,

33:49.110 --> 33:50.986
some of 'em got it somewhere else,

33:50.987 --> 33:52.821
but I tell them all the same thing.

33:52.822 --> 33:54.086
Now...

33:54.741 --> 33:57.666
I don't do refunds, but...

33:58.625 --> 34:01.312
I can give you store credit.

34:01.957 --> 34:03.499
Are you insane?

34:03.500 --> 34:06.335
Dude, it sucks out there, man.

34:06.336 --> 34:08.003
Life is hard and short

34:08.004 --> 34:10.672
and death is usually slow and painful.

34:10.674 --> 34:13.550
Or... chug this bad boy,

34:13.551 --> 34:14.885
sidle up to your favorite game,

34:14.886 --> 34:17.429
and go out doing what you love.

34:19.808 --> 34:21.850
And what happens when I snap back?

34:21.851 --> 34:23.811
That's best part.

34:23.812 --> 34:25.187
You won't.

34:25.188 --> 34:27.681
Unless you live to be, like, 103.

34:28.190 --> 34:31.443
So what do you think?

34:43.373 --> 34:45.248
Do you have Field of Fire?

34:47.268 --> 34:48.918
This way.

35:03.310 --> 35:05.098
Speedrun.

35:05.729 --> 35:07.563
See you on the other side.

35:28.084 --> 35:31.253
Look, Mommy, I made this for you.

35:31.254 --> 35:33.088
At least it's not a dog turd.

35:34.633 --> 35:37.224
I mean, do you think
about anybody but yourself?

35:38.304 --> 35:40.567
No wonder Mom left.

35:40.607 --> 35:44.433
You are the most
fearless and thoughtful,

35:44.434 --> 35:46.685
responsible person I know.

35:48.021 --> 35:50.022
I could give you a speech
about why we do what we do

35:50.023 --> 35:52.066
and why we work so hard but...

35:52.067 --> 35:54.234
you have to figure
that out for yourself.

35:56.279 --> 35:58.155
And I know that you will.

36:03.370 --> 36:04.808
What?

36:17.467 --> 36:18.634
Hello?

36:21.096 --> 36:22.763
Hello!

36:24.599 --> 36:25.933
Evan!

36:29.396 --> 36:30.979
Evan!

36:30.980 --> 36:32.815
Screw you, Val, get outta here!

36:32.816 --> 36:34.483
No, Evan, please, wait!

36:34.484 --> 36:37.236
- I... I just wanna talk.
- Bullshit, Val!

36:37.237 --> 36:38.570
You just know it sucks out there

36:38.571 --> 36:40.322
and now you want back in.

36:40.323 --> 36:42.908
No, no, I did... it's not...

36:42.909 --> 36:44.743
I do want back in, I do,

36:44.744 --> 36:46.870
but it's not because it sucks out here.

36:46.871 --> 36:48.956
Goodbye, Val!

37:07.016 --> 37:10.662
It's not about what
we get for ourselves.

37:10.687 --> 37:13.188
It's about what we give each other.

37:14.899 --> 37:17.943
I wanna be that
person... in that drawing.

37:17.944 --> 37:19.445
I wanna be that.

37:21.197 --> 37:22.531
You gotta understand,

37:22.532 --> 37:25.409
a week ago I was 19, I was kissing you

37:25.410 --> 37:26.577
at a tournament.

37:26.578 --> 37:28.011
I...

37:29.330 --> 37:31.790
I'm new at this, okay?

37:31.791 --> 37:33.751
But I wanna make it work.

37:33.752 --> 37:35.461
I'll... I'll... I'll...

37:35.462 --> 37:36.587
I'll scrub toilets,

37:36.588 --> 37:37.963
I'll do guard duty,

37:37.964 --> 37:39.214
I'll do double shifts.

37:39.215 --> 37:42.471
I'll do whatever it
takes to make it work.

37:42.762 --> 37:44.553
But I can't do it alone.

37:46.389 --> 37:49.224
Do you have any idea what it's like

37:49.225 --> 37:53.312
for 12 years of marriage
to disappear in an instant?

37:53.313 --> 37:54.563
No.

37:56.107 --> 37:58.984
I don't even know how you proposed.

37:58.985 --> 38:00.444
Are you kidding?

38:00.445 --> 38:01.528
You proposed to me.

38:01.529 --> 38:03.976
It was the best day of my life, Val.

38:04.987 --> 38:06.738
We can start over.

38:06.763 --> 38:07.993
Evan.

38:09.496 --> 38:11.176
I mean...

38:11.748 --> 38:14.663
it's not like it's the end of the world.

38:18.129 --> 38:19.755
The hell is that?

38:21.883 --> 38:24.218
- Death Lizards!
- They're people?!

38:24.219 --> 38:26.220
No, Val, they're giant
radioactive lizards.

38:26.221 --> 38:27.983
Of course they're people.

38:28.515 --> 38:30.098
Sound the alarm!

38:31.351 --> 38:33.185
I got the gate, go get the kids.

38:40.109 --> 38:42.236
Come on, everybody, get
the supplies, we gotta go!

38:42.237 --> 38:43.862
- Where, where are we going?
- To the ravine.

38:43.863 --> 38:45.572
But we can't go out
there, it's hell outside.

38:45.573 --> 38:47.032
Well, we have to.

38:47.033 --> 38:49.785
Our deputy's dead and our
sheriff is an Impulse junkie.

38:49.786 --> 38:51.328
They're gonna knock down this gate

38:51.329 --> 38:53.455
and then they're gonna kill
everybody who's left inside,

38:53.456 --> 38:54.915
so we have to go now.

38:54.916 --> 38:56.725
But this is our home.

38:58.211 --> 38:59.837
Not anymore.

39:08.179 --> 39:09.304
- Kids!
- Max!

39:09.305 --> 39:10.597
- Go with your mom.
- Sophia, come here.

39:10.598 --> 39:12.015
Come with Mommy, it's okay, it's okay.

39:12.016 --> 39:14.434
Be careful, stay... stay by the wall.

39:14.435 --> 39:15.769
All right, stay with Mommy.

39:15.770 --> 39:17.896
Stay with Mommy, it's
okay, it's all right.

39:17.897 --> 39:19.231
It's okay.

39:24.195 --> 39:26.572
- Come on, come on.
- Sheriff, we can't outrun them,

39:26.573 --> 39:28.073
it's hopeless, we're all gonna die!

39:28.074 --> 39:29.324
That's not true, is it, Mommy?

39:29.325 --> 39:31.285
No, no, no, of course not.

39:31.286 --> 39:32.953
You're with Mommy, it's okay, all right?

39:39.168 --> 39:40.568
Val!

39:41.087 --> 39:42.957
Come on, kids, come on.

39:42.982 --> 39:44.840
Hey, you guys.

39:44.841 --> 39:45.966
Guys.

39:45.967 --> 39:47.175
Val!

39:47.176 --> 39:49.011
You have to listen to
your dad, all right?

39:49.012 --> 39:50.512
Okay, promise me?

39:50.513 --> 39:51.930
Okay.

39:51.931 --> 39:53.223
All right.

39:54.225 --> 39:55.350
- Go.
- Let's go!

39:55.351 --> 39:58.103
- Come on, Sophia.
- Good girl, good girl.

39:58.104 --> 39:59.271
Val?

40:00.982 --> 40:02.316
Head for the ravine,
you'll be safe there.

40:02.317 --> 40:04.776
- What are you doing?
- My job.

40:04.777 --> 40:06.570
I'll hold them off for as long as I can.

40:06.571 --> 40:07.863
I'll send a flare when it's safe.

40:07.864 --> 40:09.740
You don't have to do this.

40:15.121 --> 40:16.413
I love you.

40:16.414 --> 40:18.081
Go, go!

40:18.082 --> 40:19.458
Go!

41:09.258 --> 41:10.676
This is it?

41:10.677 --> 41:12.344
One lousy bitch?

41:18.768 --> 41:20.102
Roy?

41:21.312 --> 41:22.854
I was wondering what
kind of idiot stands

41:22.855 --> 41:26.233
in the middle of town square
like a wannabe bad-ass.

41:26.234 --> 41:28.151
But duh!

41:28.152 --> 41:29.936
Speedrun.

41:29.961 --> 41:31.613
Last chance, Roy.

41:31.614 --> 41:34.616
You need to crawl back to
whatever hole you came out of.

41:35.785 --> 41:38.328
That's not how it works, Speedrun.

41:38.329 --> 41:39.889
It works like this.

41:40.248 --> 41:42.363
First we're gonna kill you...

41:42.875 --> 41:44.767
and then we're gonna eat you...

41:44.792 --> 41:46.628
and then we're gonna pay a little visit

41:46.629 --> 41:49.023
to that ravine over
there where your family

41:49.048 --> 41:50.650
thinks they're hiding out

41:50.675 --> 41:52.551
and we're gonna kill them

41:52.593 --> 41:54.779
then we're gonna eat them too.

41:54.804 --> 41:56.722
How many kids you got, Speedrun?

41:58.474 --> 42:01.018
Judging by that body it's
gotta be more than one.

42:02.311 --> 42:04.301
You're a monster.

42:04.689 --> 42:06.572
What can I say,

42:06.598 --> 42:08.567
wasteland changed me.

42:12.238 --> 42:15.824
Yeah, changed me too.

